commentary_text: Daniel Siebert will supervise the game today.
Georgia will kick the game off.
The match has just started.
Lasha Dvali (Georgia) picks out Georges Mikautadze with a fine lofted pass, but the latter wasn't able to create some space to get into shooting range.
Georgiy Tsitaishvili (Georgia) goes on a solo run, but he fails to create a chance as an opposition player blocks him.

Adam Hlozek (Czech Republic) has a great chance inside the six-yard box, shoots to the bottom left corner, but Giorgi Mamardashvili pulls off an exquisite save to deny him. Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) gets to a rebound in front of goal and sends the ball towards the crossbar. However, he couldn't beat Giorgi Mamardashvili, who shows off his superb goalkeeping ability by pulling off a great save.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) takes the corner but it's cleared.
Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) stoops for a header low near the left post from a cross, but the goalkeeper pulls off a great save!
Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia) sends the corner into the box, but Jindrich Stanek intercepts it and averts the threat.
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) produces a dangerous lofted cross into the box which is intercepted.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) bursts past a couple of players and shoots from the edge of the box, but his shot is blocked.

Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) whips a promising cross into the box, but the opposition's defence intercepts the ball. Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) gets to the rebound just outside the box, but his attempt is blocked by one of the defending players.

Zuriko Davitashvili (Georgia) races towards goal but the defender gets back well to make a challenge. Zuriko Davitashvili (Georgia) goes down in the box after a challenge from the defender. Possibly unsighted, the referee just waves play on.
Anzor Mekvabishvili (Georgia) brings an opponent down and Daniel Siebert interrupts the game.
Lukas Provod (Czech Republic) picks up a loose pass and unexpectedly unleashes a howitzer from distance, but the effort comes to nothing as a defender gets in the block.

David Jurasek (Czech Republic) attempts to find the head of one of his teammates with a promising cross into the box, but a defender outjumps the attackers and averts the threat. The referee and his assistant both point at the corner flag. Czech Republic will have an opportunity to threaten the opposition's goal.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) steps up to take the corner, but the ball just sails in among the defenders.
The resulting corner, taken by Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic), comes to nothing.
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) receives a yellow card from the referee, but it seems like a very harsh decision.
Vaclav Cerny receives a sweet cross inside the box from David Jurasek (Czech Republic), but one of the defenders rushes in bravely to intercept the ball.
Adam Hlozek (Czech Republic) blows a big chance from close range. World class save by the goalkeeper.
Goal! Adam Hlozek (Czech Republic) fires the rebound inside the left post after the ball breaks to him in the box. The score is 0:1.
The Czech Republic players halt their celebrations as referee Daniel Siebert makes the VAR signal to review the goal, most likely to ascertain if there was a handball in the build-up play.
Celebrations are cut short for Czech Republic as the referee indicates NO GOAL after the VAR review shows it was handball!
A pass from Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) is intercepted by Giorgi Mamardashvili and the move breaks down.
Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia) slaloms his way past challenges, but an opposing player does well to get the ball away.

Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) receives a slide-rule pass inside the box and has just the keeper to beat. His shot towards the bottom left corner lacks power and Giorgi Mamardashvili easily makes the save.

Adam Hlozek (Czech Republic) had a good chance to change the score. He ran towards the goal and unleashed a shot from just outside the penalty area which went towards the left side of the goal, but the goalkeeper was ready and made an amazing save.
0:13 - this is the total number of shots produced by both teams.
The ball is cleared after Georges Mikautadze (Georgia) attempted to dribble past an opposing player.
Otar Kakabadze (Georgia) blasts the ball from just outside the box, but his attempt is blocked by the defender.

A pass into the penalty area from Anzor Mekvabishvili (Georgia) is intercepted by the defence. Georgia have been awarded a corner kick. The referee and one of his assistants both point at the corner flag.
Georgiy Tsitaishvili (Georgia) swings in a dangerous cross from the resulting corner kick, but none of his teammates manage to outjump the defence.
Guram Kashia (Georgia) violates the laws of the game and is shown a deserved yellow card by the referee.
The referee is firm and issues Lukas Provod (Czech Republic) a deserved yellow card.

Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia) looks to break free, but an opposing player clears the ball away. The ball goes behind for a corner. Georgia will have an opportunity to threaten the opposition's goal.
Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia) swings in the corner, but fails to find any of his teammates. One of the defenders reacts superbly to get it clear. Good work from Georgia as they win a corner.
Jindrich Stanek leaps to collect the ball from the corner which was sent over by Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia).
Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic) sends a long ball in, but Giorgi Mamardashvili comfortably gathers the ball.
Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic) commits an ugly tackle on his opponent, but there is no caution from the referee. Georgia will take a free kick near the side line.
Georgiy Tsitaishvili (Georgia) puts a cross into the box from the free kick but it's cleared.
Daniel Siebert interrupts the game for a tactical foul by Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic). Georgia have a free kick.
We will have 2 min. of added time.
Guram Kashia (Georgia) had time and space inside the box after picking up a neat pass, but his shot low towards the middle of the goal was comfortably saved by Jindrich Stanek.
Surely that's handball by one of the Czech Republic players in the box, but the referee just waves play on!
There's a break in play and referee Daniel Siebert must have got a signal in his ear as he indicates he will check that earlier penalty claim by Georgia using VAR. This could be interesting!
The Georgia players are happy as the referee awards a PENALTY after the VAR review!
Georges Mikautadze (Georgia) is heading towards the penalty spot to take it.
GOAL! That's a great strike from the spot by Georges Mikautadze (Georgia) into the right of the net, giving goalkeeper Jindrich Stanek no chance!

A defence-splitting pass is taken in his stride by Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) in the box. Without even looking up he drills a shot towards the bottom left corner, but Giorgi Mamardashvili pulls off a brilliant save. Czech Republic have been awarded a corner kick.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) sends in the corner, but fails to find the head of any of his teammates, allowing the defence to clear.
The match has reached half-time.
The half-time break is over and the second half is about to start.
The game is interrupted now, Georges Mikautadze (Georgia) picks up a knock and the physio has to come on.
David Jurasek (Czech Republic) is booked after bringing down an opponent. Daniel Siebert had an easy-decision to make.
Georgiy Tsitaishvili (Georgia) sends a pass into the box, but his attempt is thwarted and cleared.
Georgiy Tsitaishvili (Georgia) swings a cross into the box, but it's far too close to Jindrich Stanek, who smothers the ball.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) sends a long ball forward to David Jurasek, but he put too much power and the chance is gone. The ball is out of play. Georgia will take a throw-in.
Tomas Holes (Czech Republic) swings it in and Patrik Schick gets on the end of it, but Giorgi Mamardashvili shows good awareness and comes off his line to thwart the move.
Tomas Holes (Czech Republic) is booked.
Vaclav Cerny (Czech Republic) finds himself behind the opposition's defence, but the game is stopped for offside.
That will be all from Vaclav Cerny who is being replaced by the fresh legs of Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic).
Ivan Hasek has decided to substitute Adam Hlozek and he is replaced by Ondrej Lingr (Czech Republic).

Ondrej Lingr almost found himself in a promising position after Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic) tried to send a defence-splitting pass, but one of the defenders reacts well and makes a timely interception. The ball goes out of play. Czech Republic are awarded a corner kick.
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) takes the corner, but it's intercepted by the defender.

A rebound on the edge of the box falls to the feet of the unmarked David Jurasek (Czech Republic). He doesn't hesitate and shoots towards goal, but unfortunately for him it hits one of his own teammates.
Golden chance! Anzor Mekvabishvili (Georgia) meets a cross in the box and finds some space for a shot. He produces an inaccurate effort that goes wide of the right post.
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) will deliver the ball into the penalty box from a corner kick.
Ondrej Lingr (Czech Republic) sees his header crash off the left post after meeting a corner kick inside the six-yard box. The goalkeeper would have been helpless.
Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) latches on a rebound and puts the ball inside the net by using body.
Surely that's handball by one of the Georgia players in the box, but the referee just waves play on!
Referee Daniel Siebert makes the VAR signal and is going to check whether it's a penalty for Czech Republic. Let's see what happens!
Here comes the ref's decision after the VAR review. It's not penalty to Czech Republic as the referee indicates there was no infringement!
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) goes over to take the corner kick and it looks like he will swing the ball into the penalty box.
Vladimir Coufal sends over an inswinging corner and Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic) gets his head on the ball, but it goes just wide of the left post.
Here comes a substitution. Georgiy Tsitaishvili is given a rest as he is replaced by Luka Lochoshvili (Georgia).
Willy Sagnol prepares a substitution. Zuriko Davitashvili is replaced by Giorgi Chakvetadze (Georgia).
A snap shot by Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic) from the edge of the area flies towards the bottom left corner, but Giorgi Mamardashvili produces a good save to thwart him.
Patrik Schick (Czech Republic) is asking for medical treatment, but he will have to leave the pitch in order to receive help from the physio.
Ivan Hasek is forced to make a change. Patrik Schick is unable to continue due to injury, Mojmir Chytil (Czech Republic) comes on.
Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic) sends a teasing cross into the area, but Giorgi Mamardashvili intercepts the ball.
Giorgi Chakvetadze lays the ball off to Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia), who hurriedly shoots from long range and sends the ball high over the bar into row Z.
Ladislav Krejci (Czech Republic) collects an inch-perfect pass and strikes the ball from far out, but his shot is blocked. The ball is out of play and Czech Republic manage to earn a corner.
Vladimir Coufal (Czech Republic) launches an inaccurate corner kick into the penalty area.
David Jurasek (Czech Republic) covers his face with his hands after wasting a promising chance. He takes the rebound on the edge of the box but blazes the ball high over the crossbar.
Ondrej Lingr (Czech Republic) breaks past challenges inside the box, but puts too much pace on his pass to Matej Jurasek. The ball goes out of play and Georgia will have a goal kick.
Khvicha Kvaratskhelia (Georgia) attempts to find Otar Kakabadze, but puts far too much on the pass and the chance is gone. The ball is off of the pitch and it's a goal kick for Czech Republic.
David Jurasek delivers a perfect cross for Mojmir Chytil (Czech Republic), who has simple job scoring from close range but somehow contrives to send the ball just wide of the right post.

Ondrej Lingr (Czech Republic) does well to control a poor pass on the edge of the box then shoots towards the bottom right corner. Giorgi Mamardashvili is out of position but leaps to make a brilliant save.
Ondrej Lingr (Czech Republic) decides to speed play up with a short corner kick.
Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic) receives an accurate pass and attempts to threaten the goalkeeper with his long-range strike. Unfortunately for him, his effort goes high above the crossbar.
Tomas Soucek (Czech Republic) has tested the patience of referee Daniel Siebert and goes into the book for a previous late challenge.
The referee allows time for a substitution. Lukas Provod will be replaced by Antonin Barak (Czech Republic).
Ivan Hasek has decided to introduce fresh legs, with Petr Sevcik (Czech Republic) replacing David Jurasek.
The referee stops play so that a substitution can be made and Solomon Kvirkvelia trots off the pitch and is replaced by Giorgi Gvelesiani (Georgia).
The substitution is prepared. Saba Lobjanidze (Georgia) joins the action as a substitute, replacing Khvicha Kvaratskhelia.
Unsporting behaviour by Giorgi Gvelesiani (Georgia). This is a yellow card! Giorgi Gvelesiani (Georgia) is not happy with the decision, but from our point of view it was clear.
Anzor Mekvabishvili (Georgia) receives a yellow card from the referee as expected.
The defence is alert as they clear a dangerous cross from Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic). Czech Republic will take a corner kick.
Czech Republic take a short corner kick.
Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic) quickly takes the corner kick with a short pass.
The attendance for today's match is 46524.
Saba Lobjanidze (Georgia) produces a dangerous low pass into the penalty area, but the defence manage to cut it out. Georgia have been awarded a corner kick.
That's the end of the game for Georges Mikautadze, who is replaced by Giorgi Kvilitaia (Georgia).
Giorgi Chakvetadze (Georgia) puts a dangerous cross into the box, but the corner is cleared by the first man.
Tomas Soucek (Czech Republic) attempts to send over a cross in order to find one of his teammates, but an opposition defender averts the danger by intercepting the effort.
There will be a minimum of 5 min. of added time.
Good movement by Tomas Soucek (Czech Republic), but he can't find any of his teammates as the cross is poor.
Matej Jurasek (Czech Republic) picks up a pass and unleashes a low shot towards goal, but he can't generate enough power to trouble Giorgi Mamardashvili.
This is an obvious ploy to delay the restart of play from Giorgi Kochorashvili (Georgia). Giorgi Kochorashvili (Georgia) is given a fully deserved yellow card.
Tomas Holes (Czech Republic) creates a yard of space for himself and tries an effort from distance, but it's blocked.
Good chance! Giorgi Chakvetadze laid the ball off to Saba Lobjanidze (Georgia) inside the box, he ducked inside his man and rifled a shot in at goal that skimmed the top of the bar.
There will be no more action in this match as the referee signals full time.
